<p>
    Inside the office is quite spacious, with a large brown desk with a computer on it, a couple of chairs, a couch, and a few bookshelves. The doctor is sitting behind the desk, and he looks up from his papers to greet you.
</p>

<p>
    He's a young-looking man, probably entering his thirties, with dark ebony skin that contrasts against his emerald-green gaze; it almost feels like he's scanning every part of you with them. His black shoulder-length hair gently sways in the wind; although that's likely due to the standing fan facing his desk . A name card pinned to his white doctor coat shows you his name, Dr. Fertilo. 
</p>

<p>
    The man beckons you to a seat in front of his table. 
    <span class="maleSpeech">
        â€œMiss <<PC>>, I presume. Please have a seat before we discuss,â€
    </span> he says. For just a moment, you feel at ease, it almost feels as if his voice has a calming effect. You sit down on the chair offered while the doctor clears his table.
</p>

<p>
    <span class="femaleSpeech">
        â€œI shouldn't be surprised you know my name already, with everything else you sent in that letter,â€
    </span> you tell him just as he finishes, but quickly end it once you notice that it's not the ideal way to start. 
    <span class="femaleSpeech">
        â€œ<i>Ahem.</i> What I wanted to say was, how? How did you find out about me and my situation? Why are you looking for me? I'm definitely sure I wasn't on the news after the accident.â€
    </span>
</p>

<p>
    Mr Fertilo lets out a small laugh and smiles at you. 
    <span class="maleSpeech">
        â€œYou may be unsure of it now, but there's no reason to be so stiff here. We're in the same boat, after all.â€
    </span> 
    He presses a button and speaks to his intercom in a hushed tone./*, telling somebody to bring someone he refers as <i>"her"</i> to his office.*/
</p>

<p>
    An energetic feminine voice replies, but you're only able to make out, 
    <span class="femaleSpeech2">
        â€œOn it, boss!â€
    </span> before he turns off the intercom.
</p>

<p>
    <span class="maleSpeech">
        â€œThe next person to come here should be able to answer your first question, but till then, let me explain everything else, starting with myselfâ€¦â€
    </span> 
    The smile on his face partially fades into a more serious look. 
    <span class="maleSpeech">
        â€œIt seems that my receptionist forgot to give you my name, since I noticed you staring at my name tag earlier. <i>Sigh.</i> My secretary told me about her current condition. Don't worry about it, she'll be fine. Maybe I need to revisit the rules about the types of "pranks" not allowed hereâ€¦
    </span>
</p>

<p>
    <span class="maleSpeech">
        Alright. My name is Mr. 
        <span class="otherSpeech">
            Fertilo 
        </span>
        Guvala, the head doctor and owner of Fertilo Inc, but most people call me Dr. Fert. As for why I reached out to you...â€
    </span> 
    He clears his throat and continues, 
    <span class="maleSpeech">
        â€œYou and I share a common background. We are both subjects of <strong>illicit genetic experimentation</strong>.â€
    </span>
</p>

<p>
    <span class="femaleSpeech">
        â€œI seeâ€¦â€
    </span> 
    You stand up from your seat and look at Mr. Fert in disbelief. 
    <span class="femaleSpeech">
        â€œY'know, I thought I could get answers here, but it turns out that you're delusional. I'm delusional. This is bullshit. Nothing here makes sense. Genetic experimentation? Nah, that only happens in movies. This can't be real. I probably hit my head way too hard.â€
    </span>
</p>

<p class="maleSpeech">
    â€œMiss <<PC>>, please try to listen-â€
</p>

<p class="femaleSpeech">
    â€œNo! I can't accept this. I won't accept this. It isn't real. I didn't lose my only job. I didn't have that dream earlier. I don't have any dumb tattoo on my belly.â€
</p>

